1 Mixed model equation

\[ \left[ \begin{matrix} \mathbf{X}^{'}\mathbf{R}^{-1}\mathbf{X} & \mathbf{X}^{'}\mathbf{R}^{-1}\mathbf{Z}\\ \mathbf{Z}^{'}\mathbf{R}^{-1}\mathbf{X} & (\mathbf{Z}^{'}\mathbf{R}^{-1}\mathbf{Z} + \mathbf{G}^{-1}) \end{matrix} \right] \left[ \begin{matrix} \boldsymbol{\hat{\beta}} \\ \mathbf{\hat{u}} \end{matrix} \right] = \left[ \begin{matrix} \mathbf{X}^{'}\mathbf{R}^{-1}\mathbf{y} \\ \mathbf{Z}^{'}\mathbf{R}^{-1}\mathbf{y} \end{matrix} \right] \]

3.1 Pedigree matrix

ped <- read.csv("pedpprevi.csv")

allparents <- unique(c(ped$Parent1, ped$Parent2))
missingparents <- setdiff(allparents, ped$Hybrid)
missingparents <- missingparents[!is.na(missingparents)]

founders <- data.frame(
  Hybrid = missingparents,
  Parent1 = NA,
  Parent2 = NA,
  train = NA,
  test = NA,
  vcf = NA
)

pedcomplete <- bind_rows(ped, founders)

pedagh <- data.frame(
  individual = pedcomplete$Hybrid,
  father = pedcomplete$Parent1,
  mother = pedcomplete$Parent2
)

pedagh <- pedagh %>%
  mutate(
    father = ifelse(is.na(father), "0", father),
    mother = ifelse(is.na(mother), "0", mother)
  )

A <- Amatrix(pedagh, ploidy = 2)

4 Multi-Environment

4.1 Presence–absence heatmap

data$env = as.factor(data$env)
data$gen = as.factor(data$gen)

amb = model.matrix(~-1 + env, data = data)
ind = model.matrix(~-1 + gen, data = data)

amb_ind = t(amb) %*% ind

colnames(amb_ind) = sub("G","",colnames(amb_ind))
rownames(amb_ind) = sub("E","",rownames(amb_ind))

amb_ind = ifelse(amb_ind == 0, "Absence","Presence")

Heatmap(amb_ind,   show_column_names = FALSE,column_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 5),
        row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 8), col = c("lightgray","tomato"),heatmap_legend_param = list(title=""))

4.6.1 Comparing FA models

In the FA framework, different numbers of factors can be considered for the analysis of experimental trials. To determine the most appropriate model, we can use the Akaike Information Criterion (AIC) and the Average Semi-Variance Ratio (ASR).

source("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/saulo-chaves/May_b_useful/refs/heads/main/fa_outs.R")

fa.models = list(fa1, fa2, fa3)
fa.res = lapply(fa.models, function(x) fa.outs(x, name.env = "env",
                                               name.gen = "gen"))
diagnos = do.call(rbind,lapply(fa.res, function(x) x$diagnostics))
rownames(diagnos) = c("fa1", "fa2", "fa3"); diagnos[,'ASVR']
rownames(diagnos) = c("fa1", "fa2", "fa3"); diagnos[,'aic']
fa7 = fa.res[[3]]

4.6.2 FAST

\[\begin{equation} \mathrm{OP}_i \;=\; \frac{1}{m} \sum_{j=1}^{m} \hat{\lambda}_{j1}\,\hat{f}_{i1}. \end{equation}\] \[\begin{equation} \mathrm{RMSD}_i \;=\; \sqrt{ \frac{1}{m} \sum_{j=1}^{m} \hat{e}_{ij}^{\,2} }. \end{equation}\]

num.gen <- nlevels(data$gen)
rel = fa7$blups |>
  dplyr::reframe(rel = 1-(mean(std.error^2)/mean(diag(fa7$Gvcov))), .by = gen)
FAST = data.frame(
  env = fa7$blups$env,
  gen = fa7$blups$gen,
  RMSD = (fa7$blups$marginal - (kronecker(fa7$rot.loads[,1], diag(num.gen)) %*%
                                  fa7$rot.scores[,1]))^2
) |> dplyr::reframe(RMSD = sqrt(mean(RMSD)), .by = gen) |>
  dplyr::mutate(OP = mean(fa7$rot.loads[,1]) * fa7$rot.scores[,1],
                index = 2*((OP-mean(OP))/sqrt(var(OP))) - ((RMSD-mean(RMSD))/sqrt(var(RMSD))),
                rel = rel$rel)




FAST |> ggplot(aes(x = RMSD, y = OP)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = rel)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, linetype = 'dashed') +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed") +
  gghighlight(gen %in% FAST[order(FAST$index, decreasing = T),'gen'][1:8]) +
  geom_label_repel(aes(label = gen), size = 2, box.padding = .5,
                   max.overlaps = 30) +
  labs(colour = "Reliability") +
  scale_colour_viridis_c() +
  labs(x = "Root mean square deviation", y = "Overall performance")
